## 1. ABSTRACT

The Lease Management System is a Salesforce-based solution designed to automate property lease operations. This system manages properties, tenants, lease agreements, and payments through a centralized digital platform. Key features include automated email notifications, approval workflows, trigger-based validations, and scheduled reminders. The project demonstrates practical implementation of Salesforce development tools including custom objects, Lightning apps, Apex programming, and Flow automation to streamline lease management processes and reduce manual effort by approximately 70%.

---

## 2. INTRODUCTION

### 2.1 Problem Statement
Traditional lease management involves manual tracking, paper documents, and disconnected communication, leading to inefficiencies and errors.

### 2.2 Solution
A cloud-based Salesforce application that centralizes data, automates workflows, and provides real-time visibility into lease operations.

### 2.3 Technology Stack

| Component | Technology |
|-----------|------------|
| Platform | Salesforce Developer Edition |
| UI Framework | Lightning Experience |
| Programming | Apex |
| Automation | Flows, Triggers |
| Database | Custom Objects |

### 2.4 Project Objectives

| Objective | Expected Outcome |
|-----------|------------------|
| Data Centralization | Single source of truth |
| Process Automation | 70% reduction in manual tasks |
| Payment Tracking | 95% on-time payments |
| Communication | Automated notifications |

