### STEP 7: Approval Process

**Purpose:** Approve high-value leases (Rent > ₹50,000)

**Navigation:** Setup → Approval Processes → Create New

#### Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Object | Lease |
| Process Name | High_Value_Lease_Approval |
| Entry Criteria | Monthly_Rent__c > 50000 |
| Approver | Property Manager |

#### Approval Actions

| Stage | Action Type | Details |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| Submission | Field Update | Status = "Pending Approval" |
| Submission | Email Alert | Notify approver |
| Approval | Field Update | Status = "Approved" |
| Approval | Email Alert | Send approval email to tenant |
| Rejection | Field Update | Status = "Rejected" |
| Rejection | Email Alert | Send rejection email |

---

### STEP 8: Apex Trigger

**Purpose:** Prevent multiple tenants for same property

#### Trigger Code

```apex
trigger TenantTrigger on Tenant__c (before insert) {
    testHandler.preventInsert(Trigger.new);
}
```

#### Handler Class

```apex
public class testHandler {
    public static void preventInsert(List newlist) {
        Set existingPropertyIds = new Set();
        
        for (Tenant__c existingTenant : [SELECT Id, Property__c 
                                          FROM Tenant__c 
                                          WHERE Property__c != null]) {
            existingPropertyIds.add(existingTenant.Property__c);
        }
        
        for (Tenant__c newTenant : newlist) {
            if (newTenant.Property__c != null && 
                existingPropertyIds.contains(newTenant.Property__c)) {
                newTenant.addError('A tenant can have only one property');
            }
        }
    }
}
```

#### Test Scenarios

| Scenario | Expected Result |
|----------|-----------------|
| Property unoccupied | Tenant created successfully |
| Property already occupied | Error: "A tenant can have only one property" |

---

### STEP 9: Flow Creation

**Purpose:** Send email when payment is recorded

**Navigation:** Setup → Flows → New Flow → Record-Triggered Flow

#### Flow Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Flow Name | Payment_Notification_Flow |
| Object | Payment |
| Trigger | Record is created |
| Condition | Payment_Status__c = "Paid" |

#### Flow Elements

| Element | Type | Purpose |
|---------|------|---------|
| Get Records | Query | Fetch tenant email |
| Send Email | Action | Send confirmation email |

**Flow Logic:**
1. Payment record created with Status = "Paid"
2. Get tenant details from lookup
3. Send payment confirmation email
4. End flow

---

### STEP 10: Scheduled Apex

**Purpose:** Daily payment reminders

#### Scheduler Class

```apex
global class PaymentReminderScheduler implements Schedulable {
    global void execute(SchedulableContext sc) {
        Date reminderDate = Date.today().addDays(3);
        
        List upcomingPayments = [
            SELECT Id, Tenant__r.Email__c, Amount_Paid__c, Due_Date__c
            FROM Payment__c
            WHERE Due_Date__c = :reminderDate
            AND Payment_Status__c = 'Pending'
        ];
        
        List emails = 
            new List();
        
        for (Payment__c payment : upcomingPayments) {
            Messaging.SingleEmailMessage email = 
                new Messaging.SingleEmailMessage();
            email.setToAddresses(
                new String[] { payment.Tenant__r.Email__c });
            email.setSubject('Payment Reminder');
            email.setPlainTextBody('Payment of ₹' + 
                payment.Amount_Paid__c + ' due on ' + 
                payment.Due_Date__c);
            emails.add(email);
        }
        
        if (!emails.isEmpty()) {
            Messaging.sendEmail(emails);
        }
    }
}
```

#### Schedule Job

```apex
String cronExp = '0 0 9 * * ?'; // Daily at 9 AM
String jobName = 'Daily Payment Reminder';
System.schedule(jobName, cronExp, new PaymentReminderScheduler());
```

